The paper discusses research on comics from a computer science perspective, with a focus on low-level document image analysis, user interaction, and content generation. This suggests that the paper could fall under multiple sub-categories, including multimedia (cs.MM), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and digital libraries (cs.DL). However, given the emphasis on image analysis and user interaction, cs.MM and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories.
